  "text": "(Within some models there are exception alerts, thus the presence of the exception alert overrules the toxic effect; this applies, for instance, to the presence of a sulfonic group which can cancel the genotoxic activity of the aromatic amine.) The structural alert is the ontology which defines the family, but in some cases the structural alert is supported by one single chemical, thus this is conceptually very similar to the one-to-one read-across model. This is the case, for instance, in the rule for genotoxicity of SA_1: Acyl halides [CITATION_1] .",
